name: precorrin-6B C5,15-methyltransferase (decarboxylating)
reaction: 2 S-adenosyl-L-methionine + precorrin-6B = 2 S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + precorrin-8X + CO2 (overall reaction) [RN:R05149]; (1a) S-adenosyl-L-methionine + precorrin-6B = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + precorrin-7 + CO2; (1b) S-adenosyl-L-methionine + precorrin-7 = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + precorrin-8X
comment: The enzyme, which participates in the aerobic adenosylcobalamin biosynthesis pathway, has S-adenosyl-L-methionine-dependent methyltransferase and decarboxylase activities. The enzyme is a fusion protein with two active sites; one catalyses the methylation at C15 and the decarboxylation, while the other catalyses the methylation at C5.

references.title: Biosynthesis of vitamin B12 in Pseudomonas denitrificans: the biosynthetic sequence from precorrin-6y to precorrin-8x is catalyzed by the cobL gene product.
An enzyme-trap approach allows isolation of intermediates in cobalamin biosynthesis.
